cx-tools-view-guidelines-link:
{{notranslate}}

Link to translation guideline in the target language wiki. Give the absolute URL of a translation guidelines page in target language.

To change the URL shown to users in your wiki, get an administrator in your wiki to change the local message MediaWiki:Cx-tools-view-guidelines-link there. Don't edit this message on translatewiki, it has no effect.

cx-tools-mt-provider-title:
An item in a menu in the machine translation tool card on Special:ContentTranslation. The menu lists different available machine translation providers for this language.
* $1 is the name of the provider, such as Apertium, Microsoft Translator, Google Translate, etc.
{{Identical|Use}}

cx-page-selector-widget-nearby-label:
Label used in "New translation" dialog, above the suggestions based on user's current location, showing pages in proximity to the user.
It is only shown if the user has enabled the location access in his device.
{{Identical|Nearby}}

cx-translation-filter-label-all-language:
Refers to "all" as in "all languages". (This may have to match the gender of "languages" for languages which inflect adjectives for this.) Used as label for translation filter in Content Translation dashboard. Can be used on both source and target language filter, when no particular source or target language is chosen.

It is recommended to make this as short as possible, because it is shown on a small button that can't be made larger.
{{Identical|All}}
